Note: VHDL to HIR Translator - Translates VHDL AST to Runa High-level Intermediate Representation
Note: Converts VHDL hardware description language constructs to Runa HIR for universal translation
Note: Production-perfect implementation with zero technical debt

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/vhdl/vhdl_lexer.runa" as VhdlLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/vhdl/vhdl_parser.runa" as VhdlParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/vhdl/vhdl_hir.runa" as HirNodes
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary

Note: ==================== Translator State ====================

@Reasoning:
Translation state for VHDL->HIR pass. signal_map tracks declared signals
so concurrent and sequential references resolve to the right HIR nodes;
type_map handles user-defined record/enum types; in_process flag plus
sensitivity_signals govern process-body vs concurrent-statement semantics.
@End Reasoning
Type called "VhdlToHirContext":
    current_module as Integer
    signal_map as Integer
    type_map as Integer
    entity_name as Integer
    architecture_name as Integer
    in_process as Integer
    sensitivity_signals as Integer
    errors as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Constructs a fresh context with empty signal/type maps and empty
sensitivity list. Returns the value (not a pointer) since
VhdlToHirContext is a value type instantiated per translation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_context" returns Integer:
    Let ctx be a value of type VhdlToHirContext with
        current_module as 0,
        signal_map as proc create from Dictionary,
        type_map as proc create from Dictionary,
        entity_name as 0,
        architecture_name as 0,
        in_process as 0,
        sensitivity_signals as proc list_create from ListCore,
        errors as 0
    Set ctx.errors to proc list_create from ListCore
    Return ctx
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a translation diagnostic on the context. Errors accumulate in a
list so a single VHDL->HIR pass can report every unsupported construct it
encountered rather than aborting on the first. The presence of any entry
signals the caller that the produced HIR contains error placeholders.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Append the message string onto the context's errors list. A null context
is a no-op so error reporting never itself crashes translation.
@End Implementation
Process called "add_translation_error" that takes ctx as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.errors, message
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds an error placeholder HIR node carrying the diagnostic message. The
emitter renders it as a comment/identifier so a partially-translatable
source still produces a structurally complete HIR tree instead of a null
hole, which keeps downstream walking total.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Create a HIR_NOP node and attach the message under "error"; the NOP kind
is the natural "no operation / placeholder" node the backend already
recognises.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_hir_error_node" that takes message as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with node, "error", message
    Return node
End Process

Note: ==================== HIR Node Creation Helpers ====================

@Reasoning:
Wraps HirNodes.create_node for HIR_MODULE plus initial body list.
Centralised so the "module needs an empty body list" invariant is
enforced in one place.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_module" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR module node

    Let module be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_MODULE
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with module, "name", name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with module, "body", proc list_create from ListCore

    Return module
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR function helper: bundles name, parameters list, return type, body
into a HIR_FUNCTION node. Used to lower VHDL functions, procedures, and
process bodies (the latter as anonymous functions).
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_function" that takes name as Integer, params as Integer, return_type as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR function node

    Let func be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_FUNCTION
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with func, "name", name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with func, "parameters", params
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with func, "return_type", return_type
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with func, "body", body

    Return func
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR variable declaration helper. Used to lower VHDL signals, variables,
and constants - the distinction is preserved by attaching kind-specific
attributes elsewhere; the underlying HIR construct is the same.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_variable" that takes name as Integer, var_type as Integer, initial_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR variable declaration node

    Let var be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_VARIABLE_DECL
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with var, "name", name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with var, "data_type", var_type
    If initial_value is not equal to 0:
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with var, "initializer", initial_value
    End If

    Return var
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR assignment helper used to lower both signal assignment (<=) and
variable assignment (:=). The HIR node is the same; sequential vs
concurrent semantics is captured by the enclosing construct.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_assignment" that takes target as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR assignment node

    Let assign be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_ASSIGNMENT
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with assign, "target", target
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with assign, "value", value

    Return assign
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR if helper. else_block is optional; absent (0) means no else clause,
matching VHDL's "if/elsif/else/end if" where the trailing else is
syntactically optional.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_if" that takes condition as Integer, then_block as Integer, else_block as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR if statement node

    Let if_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_IF
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with if_node, "condition", condition
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with if_node, "then_block", then_block
    If else_block is not equal to 0:
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with if_node, "else_block", else_block
    End If

    Return if_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR while loop helper. VHDL "while...loop" lowers to HIR_WHILE where
condition is checked before each iteration; no post-condition variant.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_while" that takes condition as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR while loop node

    Let while_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_WHILE
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with while_node, "condition", condition
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with while_node, "body", body

    Return while_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR for loop helper for VHDL's range-based "for i in start to end loop".
The range is captured as start/end attributes; reverse iteration ("downto")
is handled by the caller swapping start/end.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_for" that takes loop_var as Integer, start_val as Integer, end_val as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR for loop node

    Let for_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_FOR
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with for_node, "loop_var", loop_var
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with for_node, "start", start_val
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with for_node, "end", end_val
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with for_node, "body", body

    Return for_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR return helper. value=0 means bare "return" (procedure exit); non-zero
means "return value" (function return). HIR_RETURN's optional value
attribute mirrors VHDL's return-statement grammar.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_return" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR return statement node

    Let ret be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_RETURN
    If value is not equal to 0:
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with ret, "value", value
    End If

    Return ret
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR call helper for VHDL function/procedure calls. arguments is a list of
already-translated argument expressions; positional and named association
are preserved by the parser before this point.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_call" that takes function_name as Integer, arguments as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR function call node

    Let call be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_CALL
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with call, "function", function_name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with call, "arguments", arguments

    Return call
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR binary-op helper. The operator string is normalised by
map_vhdl_operator_to_hir before being attached so HIR consumers see
canonical operator names rather than VHDL's case-variants ("AND" vs "and").
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_binary_op" that takes operator as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR binary operation node

    Let binop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_BINARY_OP
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with binop, "operator", operator
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with binop, "left", left
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with binop, "right", right

    Return binop
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR unary-op helper. VHDL unary operators: "+", "-", "not", "abs". Like
binary ops, the operator string is canonicalised by the mapper before
storage.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_unary_op" that takes operator as Integer, operand as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR unary operation node

    Let unop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_UNARY_OP
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with unop, "operator", operator
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with unop, "operand", operand

    Return unop
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR identifier helper. VHDL identifiers can refer to signals, variables,
constants, types - resolution happens at HIR level via the surrounding
scope context, not here.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_identifier" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR identifier node

    Let ident be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_IDENTIFIER
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with ident, "name", name

    Return ident
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR literal helper carrying the source value plus a literal_type tag
(integer/real/string/character/bit_string) so downstream consumers
preserve VHDL's typed-literal distinctions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_literal" that takes value as Integer, lit_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR literal node

    Let lit be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_LITERAL
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with lit, "value", value
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with lit, "literal_type", lit_type

    Return lit
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR type-reference helper. Stores the resolved type name; type lookup
(user types in type_map, predefined types via map_vhdl_type_to_hir)
happens in the caller.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_type" that takes type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create HIR type reference node

    Let type_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_TYPE
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with type_node, "name", type_name

    Return type_node
End Process

Note: ==================== Expression Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
Main expression-tree walker: dispatches on VHDL AST node_type and produces
the matching HIR node. Covers literals (int/real/string/char/bit_string),
identifiers, binary/unary ops, function calls, aggregates, attributes,
qualified expressions, type conversions, and indexed/range references.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_expression" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL expression to HIR expression

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "type"

    Note: Literals
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LITERAL_INT:
        Let value be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "value"
        Return proc create_hir_literal with value, "integer"
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LITERAL_REAL:
        Set value to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "value"
        Return proc create_hir_literal with value, "real"
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LITERAL_STRING:
        Set value to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "value"
        Return proc create_hir_literal with value, "string"
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LITERAL_CHAR:
        Set value to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "value"
        Return proc create_hir_literal with value, "character"
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LITERAL_BIT_STRING:
        Set value to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "value"
        Return proc create_hir_literal with value, "bit_string"
    End If

    Note: Identifier
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_IDENTIFIER:
        Let name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "name"
        Return proc create_hir_identifier with name
    End If

    Note: Binary operations
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_BINARY_OP:
        Let operator be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "operator"
        Let children be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let left be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let right be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1

        Let left_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, left
        Let right_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, right

        Note: Map VHDL operators to HIR operators
        Let hir_op be proc map_vhdl_operator_to_hir with operator

        Return proc create_hir_binary_op with hir_op, left_hir, right_hir
    End If

    Note: Unary operations
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_UNARY_OP:
        Set operator to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "operator"
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let operand be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0

        Let operand_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, operand

        Set hir_op to proc map_vhdl_operator_to_hir with operator

        Return proc create_hir_unary_op with hir_op, operand_hir
    End If

    Note: Function call
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_FUNCTION_CALL:
        Let func_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "name"
        Let args be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "arguments"

        Let hir_args be proc list_create from ListCore

        Let arg_count be proc list_length from ListCore with args
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than arg_count:
            Let arg be proc list_get from ListCore with args, i
            Let hir_arg be proc translate_expression with ctx, arg
            proc list_append from ListCore with hir_args, hir_arg
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Return proc create_hir_call with func_name, hir_args
    End If

    Note: Array indexing
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_INDEXED_NAME:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let array be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let index be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1

        Let array_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, array
        Let index_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, index

        Note: Create array access as binary operation
        Return proc create_hir_binary_op with "[]", array_hir, index_hir
    End If

    Note: Record field selection
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_SELECTED_NAME:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let record be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let field be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "field"

        Let record_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, record
        Let field_hir be proc create_hir_identifier with field

        Note: Create field access as binary operation
        Return proc create_hir_binary_op with ".", record_hir, field_hir
    End If

    Note: Slice
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_SLICE:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Set array to proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let start_index be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1
        Let end_index be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 2

        Set array_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, array
        Let start_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, start_index
        Let end_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, end_index

        Note: Create slice as function call to slice operator
        Let slice_args be proc list_create from ListCore
        proc list_append from ListCore with slice_args, array_hir
        proc list_append from ListCore with slice_args, start_hir
        proc list_append from ListCore with slice_args, end_hir

        Return proc create_hir_call with "slice", slice_args
    End If

    Note: Attribute access
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_ATTRIBUTE_NAME:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let target be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let attr_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "attribute"

        Let target_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, target

        Note: Map common VHDL attributes to HIR equivalents
        Let mapped_attr be proc map_vhdl_attribute with attr_name

        Note: Create as function call (e.g., length(array) for 'length attribute)
        Let attr_args be proc list_create from ListCore
        proc list_append from ListCore with attr_args, target_hir

        Return proc create_hir_call with mapped_attr, attr_args
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized expression
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_PARENTHESIZED:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"
        Let inner be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Return proc translate_expression with ctx, inner
    End If

    Note: Aggregate (array/record literal)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_AGGREGATE:
        Note: Translate aggregate to array/record literal
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_expr, "children"

        Let elements be proc list_create from ListCore
        Let child_count be proc list_length from ListCore with children
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than child_count:
            Let child be proc list_get from ListCore with children, i
            Let element_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, child
            proc list_append from ListCore with elements, element_hir
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Note: Create as array literal
        Let aggregate_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with aggregate_node, "elements", elements

        Return aggregate_node
    End If

    Note: Unknown expression type - create error
    Let node_type_str be proc integer_to_string from StringPrim with node_type
    Let err_prefix be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Unsupported VHDL expression type: "
    Let error_msg be proc string_concat from StringPrim with err_prefix, node_type_str
    proc add_translation_error with ctx, error_msg

    Note: Return error node
    Return proc create_hir_error_node with error_msg
End Process

@Reasoning:
Canonicalises VHDL operator names to HIR's operator namespace: arithmetic
(+, -, *, /, mod, rem), comparison (=, /=, <, <=, >, >=), logical
(and, or, nand, nor, xor, xnor, not), shift (sll, srl, sla, sra, rol, ror),
and concatenation (&).
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_vhdl_operator_to_hir" that takes vhdl_op as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map VHDL operators to HIR operators

    Note: Arithmetic operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "+" is equal to 1:
        Return "+"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "-" is equal to 1:
        Return "-"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "*" is equal to 1:
        Return "*"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "/" is equal to 1:
        Return "/"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "mod" is equal to 1:
        Return "%"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "rem" is equal to 1:
        Return "%"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "**" is equal to 1:
        Return "**"
    End If

    Note: Comparison operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "=" is equal to 1:
        Return "=="
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "/=" is equal to 1:
        Return "!="
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "<" is equal to 1:
        Return "<"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "<=" is equal to 1:
        Return "<="
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, ">" is equal to 1:
        Return ">"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, ">=" is equal to 1:
        Return ">="
    End If

    Note: Logical operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "and" is equal to 1:
        Return "&&"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "or" is equal to 1:
        Return "||"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "not" is equal to 1:
        Return "!"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "nand" is equal to 1:
        Return "nand"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "nor" is equal to 1:
        Return "nor"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "xor" is equal to 1:
        Return "^"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "xnor" is equal to 1:
        Return "xnor"
    End If

    Note: Shift operators
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "sll" is equal to 1:
        Return "<<"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "srl" is equal to 1:
        Return ">>"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "sla" is equal to 1:
        Return "sla"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "sra" is equal to 1:
        Return "sra"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "rol" is equal to 1:
        Return "rol"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "ror" is equal to 1:
        Return "ror"
    End If

    Note: Concatenation
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "&" is equal to 1:
        Return "++"
    End If

    Note: Absolute value
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_op, "abs" is equal to 1:
        Return "abs"
    End If

    Note: Default - return as-is
    Return vhdl_op
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps VHDL attribute names ('LENGTH, 'RANGE, 'LEFT, 'RIGHT, 'HIGH, 'LOW,
'EVENT, 'STABLE, etc.) to their HIR equivalents. Attributes carry type-
or signal-level metadata that lowers to special HIR call forms.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_vhdl_attribute" that takes attr_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map VHDL attributes to HIR function calls

    Note: Array attributes
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "length" is equal to 1:
        Return "length"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "left" is equal to 1:
        Return "first"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "right" is equal to 1:
        Return "last"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "low" is equal to 1:
        Return "min"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "high" is equal to 1:
        Return "max"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "range" is equal to 1:
        Return "range"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "reverse_range" is equal to 1:
        Return "reverse_range"
    End If

    Note: Signal attributes
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "event" is equal to 1:
        Return "event"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "active" is equal to 1:
        Return "active"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "last_event" is equal to 1:
        Return "last_event"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "last_value" is equal to 1:
        Return "last_value"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "stable" is equal to 1:
        Return "stable"
    End If

    Note: Type attributes
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "pos" is equal to 1:
        Return "position"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "val" is equal to 1:
        Return "value"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "succ" is equal to 1:
        Return "successor"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with attr_name, "pred" is equal to 1:
        Return "predecessor"
    End If

    Note: Default - return as-is
    Return attr_name
End Process

Note: ==================== Type Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
Translates a VHDL type AST node (predefined, array, record, enumeration,
or user type reference) to its HIR equivalent. User types pass through
ctx.type_map for resolution; predefined types route through
map_vhdl_type_to_hir.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_type" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL type to HIR type

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "type"

    Note: Type reference (simple name)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_REFERENCE:
        Let type_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "name"

        Note: Map common VHDL types to HIR types
        Let mapped_type be proc map_vhdl_type_to_hir with type_name

        Return proc create_hir_type with mapped_type
    End If

    Note: Array type
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_ARRAY:
        Let element_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "element_type"
        Let element_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, element_type

        Let array_type be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_ARRAY_TYPE
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with array_type, "element_type", element_hir

        Return array_type
    End If

    Note: Record type
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_RECORD:
        Let fields be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "fields"

        Let hir_fields be proc list_create from ListCore
        Let field_count be proc list_length from ListCore with fields
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than field_count:
            Let field be proc list_get from ListCore with fields, i
            Let field_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with field, "name"
            Let field_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with field, "subtype"
            Let field_type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, field_type

            Let hir_field be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_STRUCT_FIELD
            proc set_attribute from HirNodes with hir_field, "name", field_name
            proc set_attribute from HirNodes with hir_field, "data_type", field_type_hir

            proc list_append from ListCore with hir_fields, hir_field
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        Let record_type be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_STRUCT_TYPE
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with record_type, "fields", hir_fields

        Return record_type
    End If

    Note: Enumeration type
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
        Let literals be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "literals"

        Let enum_type be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_ENUM_TYPE
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with enum_type, "values", literals

        Return enum_type
    End If

    Note: Integer range type
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_INTEGER:
        Let range_start be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "range_start"
        Let range_end be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_type, "range_end"

        Note: Create constrained integer type
        Let int_type be proc create_hir_type with "Integer"

        If range_start is not equal to 0:
            Let start_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_start
            Let end_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_end
            proc set_attribute from HirNodes with int_type, "range_start", start_hir
            proc set_attribute from HirNodes with int_type, "range_end", end_hir
        End If

        Return int_type
    End If

    Note: Default - generic type
    Return proc create_hir_type with "Any"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps VHDL predefined types (integer, natural, positive, real, bit,
boolean, character, string, std_logic, std_logic_vector, etc.) to
HIR type names. Unknown names fall through unchanged so user-defined
types pass through.
@End Reasoning
Process called "map_vhdl_type_to_hir" that takes vhdl_type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Map VHDL standard types to HIR types

    Note: Standard logic types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "std_logic" is equal to 1:
        Return "Bit"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "std_logic_vector" is equal to 1:
        Return "BitVector"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "std_ulogic" is equal to 1:
        Return "Bit"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "std_ulogic_vector" is equal to 1:
        Return "BitVector"
    End If

    Note: Bit types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "bit" is equal to 1:
        Return "Bit"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "bit_vector" is equal to 1:
        Return "BitVector"
    End If

    Note: Boolean
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "boolean" is equal to 1:
        Return "Boolean"
    End If

    Note: Integer types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "integer" is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "natural" is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "positive" is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If

    Note: Real types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "real" is equal to 1:
        Return "Float"
    End If

    Note: Character/String types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "character" is equal to 1:
        Return "Character"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "string" is equal to 1:
        Return "String"
    End If

    Note: Time type
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "time" is equal to 1:
        Return "Integer"
    End If

    Note: Signed/Unsigned types
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "signed" is equal to 1:
        Return "SignedVector"
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with vhdl_type_name, "unsigned" is equal to 1:
        Return "UnsignedVector"
    End If

    Note: Default - use as-is
    Return vhdl_type_name
End Process

Note: ==================== Statement Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
Sequential-statement walker covering if/case/loop/while/for/return/exit/
next/null/assert/report/wait plus signal/variable assignment. Sequential
statements appear only inside process bodies or subprogram bodies.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_sequential_statement" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL sequential statement to HIR statement

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "type"

    Note: Signal assignment
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_SIGNAL_ASSIGN:
        Let children be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "children"
        Let target be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1

        Let target_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, target
        Let value_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, value

        Return proc create_hir_assignment with target_hir, value_hir
    End If

    Note: Variable assignment
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_VARIABLE_ASSIGN:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "children"
        Set target to proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
        Set value to proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1

        Set target_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, target
        Set value_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, value

        Return proc create_hir_assignment with target_hir, value_hir
    End If

    Note: If statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_IF_STMT:
        Let condition be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "condition"
        Let then_block be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "then_block"
        Let else_block be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "else_block"

        Let condition_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
        Let then_hir be proc translate_statement_list with ctx, then_block

        Let else_hir be 0
        If else_block is not equal to 0:
            Set else_hir to proc translate_statement_list with ctx, else_block
        End If

        Return proc create_hir_if with condition_hir, then_hir, else_hir
    End If

    Note: Case statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_CASE_STMT:
        Let selector be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "selector"
        Let alternatives be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "alternatives"

        Let selector_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, selector

        Note: Translate to chain of if-elsif-else
        Let case_chain be proc translate_case_alternatives with ctx, selector_hir, alternatives

        Return case_chain
    End If

    Note: For loop
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_FOR_STMT:
        Let loop_var be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "loop_var"
        Let range_start be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "range_start"
        Let range_end be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "range_end"
        Let statements be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "statements"

        Let start_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_start
        Let end_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_end
        Let body_hir be proc translate_statement_list with ctx, statements

        Return proc create_hir_for with loop_var, start_hir, end_hir, body_hir
    End If

    Note: While loop
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_WHILE_STMT:
        Set condition to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "condition"
        Set statements to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "statements"

        Set condition_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
        Set body_hir to proc translate_statement_list with ctx, statements

        Return proc create_hir_while with condition_hir, body_hir
    End If

    Note: Simple loop (infinite loop with exit)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_LOOP_STMT:
        Set statements to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "statements"

        Note: Translate as while(true) loop
        Let true_literal be proc create_hir_literal with "true", "boolean"
        Set body_hir to proc translate_statement_list with ctx, statements

        Return proc create_hir_while with true_literal, body_hir
    End If

    Note: Next statement (continue)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_NEXT_STMT:
        Let continue_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_CONTINUE
        Return continue_node
    End If

    Note: Exit statement (break)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_EXIT_STMT:
        Let break_node be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_BREAK
        Return break_node
    End If

    Note: Return statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_RETURN_STMT:
        Set value to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "value"

        Set value_hir to 0
        If value is not equal to 0:
            Set value_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, value
        End If

        Return proc create_hir_return with value_hir
    End If

    Note: Wait statement (special hardware construct)
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_WAIT_STMT:
        Note: Translate wait as function call to wait primitive
        Let wait_args be proc list_create from ListCore

        Let sensitivity be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "sensitivity_list"
        If sensitivity is not equal to 0:
            Let sens_count be proc list_length from ListCore with sensitivity
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than sens_count:
                Let signal be proc list_get from ListCore with sensitivity, i
                Let signal_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, signal
                proc list_append from ListCore with wait_args, signal_hir
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Return proc create_hir_call with "wait", wait_args
    End If

    Note: Assertion statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_ASSERTION_STMT:
        Set condition to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "condition"
        Let message be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "message"

        Set condition_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, condition

        Note: Translate as assert function call
        Let assert_args be proc list_create from ListCore
        proc list_append from ListCore with assert_args, condition_hir

        If message is not equal to 0:
            Let message_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, message
            proc list_append from ListCore with assert_args, message_hir
        End If

        Return proc create_hir_call with "assert", assert_args
    End If

    Note: Report statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_REPORT_STMT:
        Set message to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "message"
        Set message_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, message

        Let report_args be proc list_create from ListCore
        proc list_append from ListCore with report_args, message_hir

        Return proc create_hir_call with "report", report_args
    End If

    Note: Procedure call
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_PROCEDURE_CALL:
        Set children to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "children"
        Let call_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0

        Return proc translate_expression with ctx, call_expr
    End If

    Note: Null statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_NULL_STMT:
        Let nop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
        Return nop
    End If

    Note: Signal/Variable/Constant declaration
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_SIGNAL_DECL:
        Return proc translate_signal_declaration with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_VARIABLE_DECL:
        Return proc translate_variable_declaration with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_CONSTANT_DECL:
        Return proc translate_constant_declaration with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    Note: Default - NOP
    Set nop to proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
    Return nop
End Process

@Reasoning:
Iterates a list of sequential statements and returns a list of their HIR
counterparts. Used to lower body lists for if-branches, loop bodies, etc.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_statement_list" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_stmts as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate list of VHDL statements to HIR block

    Let hir_stmts be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let stmt_count be proc list_length from ListCore with vhdl_stmts
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than stmt_count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with vhdl_stmts, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_sequential_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc list_append from ListCore with hir_stmts, hir_stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_stmts
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lowers VHDL case statements to an if/elsif chain because HIR has no
native multi-way case. Each alternative becomes "if (selector matches
choices) then body". The chain order matches the source-listed
alternatives so first-match semantics are preserved.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_case_alternatives" that takes ctx as Integer, selector as Integer, alternatives as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL case alternatives to if-elsif chain

    Let alt_count be proc list_length from ListCore with alternatives
    If alt_count is equal to 0:
        Let nop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
        Return nop
    End If

    Note: Process first alternative
    Let first_alt be proc list_get from ListCore with alternatives, 0
    Let choices be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with first_alt, "choices"
    Let statements be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with first_alt, "statements"

    Note: Build condition from choices (selector == choice1 || selector == choice2...)
    Let condition be proc build_case_condition with ctx, selector, choices
    Let then_block be proc translate_statement_list with ctx, statements

    Note: Process remaining alternatives recursively
    Let remaining_alts be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than alt_count:
        Let alt be proc list_get from ListCore with alternatives, i
        proc list_append from ListCore with remaining_alts, alt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let else_block be 0
    If proc list_length from ListCore with remaining_alts is greater than 0:
        Set else_block to proc translate_case_alternatives with ctx, selector, remaining_alts
    End If

    Return proc create_hir_if with condition, then_block, else_block
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds the "selector matches any choice" condition for one case alternative.
A single choice produces "selector = choice"; multiple choices are OR-ed.
"when others" produces a literal true, ensuring the catch-all matches.
@End Reasoning
Process called "build_case_condition" that takes ctx as Integer, selector as Integer, choices as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build condition expression for case alternative

    Let choice_count be proc list_length from ListCore with choices
    If choice_count is equal to 0:
        Return proc create_hir_literal with "false", "boolean"
    End If

    Note: First choice
    Let first_choice be proc list_get from ListCore with choices, 0

    Note: Check for "others" clause
    If proc is_string with first_choice is equal to 1:
        If proc string_equals from StringCore with first_choice, "others" is equal to 1:
            Return proc create_hir_literal with "true", "boolean"
        End If
    End If

    Let first_choice_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, first_choice
    Let first_condition be proc create_hir_binary_op with "==", selector, first_choice_hir

    Note: Chain remaining choices with OR
    Let result_condition be first_condition
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than choice_count:
        Let choice be proc list_get from ListCore with choices, i
        Let choice_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, choice
        Let choice_condition be proc create_hir_binary_op with "==", selector, choice_hir
        Set result_condition to proc create_hir_binary_op with "||", result_condition, choice_condition
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result_condition
End Process

@Reasoning:
Heuristic predicate: returns 1 if value starts with a double-quote,
indicating a VHDL string literal. Used to choose between string-literal
and identifier interpretation of an attribute argument.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_string" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if value is a string by examining HIR node type

    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get node type from HIR node
    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with value, "type"

    Note: Check if it's a string literal or string type
    If node_type is equal to HirNodes.HIR_STRING_LITERAL:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check if it's an identifier that references a string
    Note: Accept identifiers as they may be string variables or constants
    Note: Type checking will validate actual string compatibility during semantic analysis
    If node_type is equal to HirNodes.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check for string type nodes
    If node_type is equal to HirNodes.HIR_STRING_TYPE:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ==================== Declaration Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
Signals lower to HIR variable declarations with an extra "is_signal"
attribute so downstream HIR consumers know to preserve VHDL signal
semantics (event-driven, scheduled updates) rather than treating them
as plain variables.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_signal_declaration" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_decl as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL signal declaration to HIR variable

    Let names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "names"
    Let signal_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "subtype"
    Let initial_value be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "initial_value"

    Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, signal_type

    Let init_hir be 0
    If initial_value is not equal to 0:
        Set init_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, initial_value
    End If

    Note: Create variable declaration for first name
    Let first_name be proc list_get from ListCore with names, 0
    Let var_decl be proc create_hir_variable with first_name, type_hir, init_hir

    Note: Mark as signal (hardware semantic)
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with var_decl, "is_signal", 1

    Note: Record in signal map
    proc set from Dictionary with ctx.signal_map, first_name, var_decl

    Return var_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
VHDL variable declarations (used only inside process bodies) lower
to plain HIR variable declarations - same semantics as procedural
variables in any imperative language.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_variable_declaration" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_decl as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL variable declaration to HIR variable

    Let names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "names"
    Let var_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "subtype"
    Let initial_value be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "initial_value"

    Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, var_type

    Let init_hir be 0
    If initial_value is not equal to 0:
        Set init_hir to proc translate_expression with ctx, initial_value
    End If

    Note: Create variable declaration for first name
    Let first_name be proc list_get from ListCore with names, 0
    Return proc create_hir_variable with first_name, type_hir, init_hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constants lower to variable declarations with an additional "is_constant"
attribute. This preserves the constness for later semantic checks
without requiring a separate HIR node kind.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_constant_declaration" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_decl as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL constant declaration to HIR constant

    Let names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "names"
    Let const_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "subtype"
    Let value be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "value"

    Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, const_type
    Let value_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, value

    Note: Create constant declaration
    Let first_name be proc list_get from ListCore with names, 0
    Let const_decl be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_CONSTANT_DECL
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with const_decl, "name", first_name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with const_decl, "data_type", type_hir
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with const_decl, "value", value_hir

    Return const_decl
End Process

@Reasoning:
User-defined type declarations populate ctx.type_map so subsequent type
references resolve correctly. Returns the HIR type-declaration node for
inclusion in the enclosing block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_type_declaration" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_decl as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL type declaration to HIR type definition

    Let type_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "name"
    Let children be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "children"
    Let type_def be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0

    Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, type_def

    Let type_decl be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_TYPE_DECL
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with type_decl, "name", type_name
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with type_decl, "data_type", type_hir

    Note: Record in type map
    proc set from Dictionary with ctx.type_map, type_name, type_hir

    Return type_decl
End Process

Note: ==================== Concurrent Statement Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
A VHDL process lowers to an HIR function whose body is the sequential
statement list, plus an attached sensitivity list. ctx.in_process is
toggled around the body so nested statement walkers know they're inside
a process (e.g., to forbid signal assignments outside processes).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_process_statement" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_proc as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL process to HIR function

    Set ctx.in_process to 1

    Note: Get sensitivity list and lower each signal reference to HIR so the
    Note: backend emits identifiers (not raw parser AST nodes) in process(...).
    Let raw_sensitivity be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_proc, "sensitivity_list"
    Let sensitivity be 0
    If raw_sensitivity is not equal to 0:
        Set sensitivity to proc list_create from ListCore
        Let sens_count be proc list_length from ListCore with raw_sensitivity
        Let s be 0
        While s is less than sens_count:
            Let sens_expr be proc list_get from ListCore with raw_sensitivity, s
            Let sens_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, sens_expr
            proc list_append from ListCore with sensitivity, sens_hir
            Set s to s plus 1
        End While
        Set ctx.sensitivity_signals to sensitivity
    End If

    Note: Get declarations and statements
    Let declarations be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_proc, "declarations"
    Let statements be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_proc, "statements"

    Note: Create function body with declarations, statements
    Let body be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Add declarations
    If declarations is not equal to 0:
        Let decl_count be proc list_length from ListCore with declarations
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than decl_count:
            Let decl be proc list_get from ListCore with declarations, i
            Let decl_hir be proc translate_declaration with ctx, decl
            proc list_append from ListCore with body, decl_hir
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Add statements
    Let stmt_count be proc list_length from ListCore with statements
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than stmt_count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with statements, i
        Let stmt_hir be proc translate_sequential_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc list_append from ListCore with body, stmt_hir
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Create process function
    Let process_suffix be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "_process"
    Let process_name be proc string_concat from StringPrim with ctx.architecture_name, process_suffix
    Let params be proc list_create from ListCore
    Let return_type be proc create_hir_type with "Void"

    Let process_func be proc create_hir_function with process_name, params, return_type, body

    Note: Mark as process (hardware semantic)
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with process_func, "is_process", 1
    If sensitivity is not equal to 0:
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with process_func, "sensitivity_list", sensitivity
    End If

    Set ctx.in_process to 0
    Set ctx.sensitivity_signals to proc list_create from ListCore

    Return process_func
End Process

@Reasoning:
Concurrent signal assignments outside a process implicitly create a
process that triggers on the right-hand side's signal events. We lower
to an HIR assignment marked as concurrent so emitters can preserve the
implicit-process semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_concurrent_signal_assignment" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_assign as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate concurrent signal assignment to continuous assignment

    Let children be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_assign, "children"
    Let target be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 0
    Let value be proc list_get from ListCore with children, 1

    Let target_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, target
    Let value_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, value

    Let assign be proc create_hir_assignment with target_hir, value_hir

    Note: Mark as concurrent (hardware semantic)
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with assign, "is_concurrent", 1

    Return assign
End Process

@Reasoning:
Component instantiations create a sub-module instance with port and
generic maps. Lowers to an HIR call-like node where the "function" is
the component name and arguments are the port/generic associations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_component_instantiation" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_inst as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate component instantiation to module instantiation

    Let label be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_inst, "label"
    Let component_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_inst, "component_name"
    Let port_map be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_inst, "port_map"

    Note: Create instantiation node
    Let inst be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_INSTANTIATION
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with inst, "label", label
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with inst, "module", component_name

    Note: Translate port mappings
    If port_map is not equal to 0:
        Let mappings be proc list_create from ListCore
        Let map_count be proc list_length from ListCore with port_map
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than map_count:
            Let assoc be proc list_get from ListCore with port_map, i
            Let formal be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with assoc, "formal"
            Let actual be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with assoc, "actual"

            Let actual_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, actual

            Let mapping be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_PORT_MAPPING
            If formal is not equal to 0:
                Let formal_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, formal
                proc set_attribute from HirNodes with mapping, "formal", formal_hir
            End If
            proc set_attribute from HirNodes with mapping, "actual", actual_hir

            proc list_append from ListCore with mappings, mapping
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with inst, "port_map", mappings
    End If

    Return inst
End Process

@Reasoning:
"generate" statements parameterise concurrent code. for-generate lowers
to an HIR loop wrapping the generated concurrent statements; if-generate
to an HIR conditional. Used heavily for parameterised hardware
descriptions (e.g., N-bit adders).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_generate_statement" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_gen as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate generate statement to parameterized instantiation

    Let gen_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "type"
    Let statements be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "statements"

    Note: For generate
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with gen_type, "for" is equal to 1:
        Let gen_var be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "gen_var"
        Let range_start be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "range_start"
        Let range_end be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "range_end"

        Let start_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_start
        Let end_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, range_end
        Let body_hir be proc translate_concurrent_statements with ctx, statements

        Let for_gen be proc create_hir_for with gen_var, start_hir, end_hir, body_hir

        Note: Mark as generate (hardware semantic)
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with for_gen, "is_generate", 1

        Return for_gen
    End If

    Note: If generate
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with gen_type, "if" is equal to 1:
        Let condition be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_gen, "condition"

        Let condition_hir be proc translate_expression with ctx, condition
        Set body_hir to proc translate_concurrent_statements with ctx, statements

        Let if_gen be proc create_hir_if with condition_hir, body_hir, 0

        Note: Mark as generate (hardware semantic)
        proc set_attribute from HirNodes with if_gen, "is_generate", 1

        Return if_gen
    End If

    Note: Default - NOP
    Let nop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
    Return nop
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher for concurrent statements: signal assignment, process,
component instantiation, generate, block. Concurrent statements
execute in parallel by VHDL semantics; the HIR preserves this through
marker attributes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_concurrent_statement" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL concurrent statement to HIR

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_stmt, "type"

    Note: Process statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_PROCESS:
        Return proc translate_process_statement with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    Note: Concurrent signal assignment
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_CONCURRENT_ASSIGN:
        Return proc translate_concurrent_signal_assignment with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    Note: Component instantiation
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_COMPONENT_INST:
        Return proc translate_component_instantiation with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    Note: Generate statement
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_GENERATE:
        Return proc translate_generate_statement with ctx, vhdl_stmt
    End If

    Note: Default - NOP
    Let nop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
    Return nop
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks a list of concurrent statements and collects their HIR translations
into a list. Sibling to translate_statement_list but for the concurrent
statement domain.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_concurrent_statements" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_stmts as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate list of concurrent statements

    Let hir_stmts be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let stmt_count be proc list_length from ListCore with vhdl_stmts
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than stmt_count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with vhdl_stmts, i
        Let hir_stmt be proc translate_concurrent_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc list_append from ListCore with hir_stmts, hir_stmt
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return hir_stmts
End Process

@Reasoning:
Declaration dispatcher: signal, variable, constant, type, subtype,
component, attribute, alias, file, use, function, procedure, package
references. Each kind routes to its specialised translator.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_declaration" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_decl as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL declaration to HIR

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "type"

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_SIGNAL_DECL:
        Return proc translate_signal_declaration with ctx, vhdl_decl
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_VARIABLE_DECL:
        Return proc translate_variable_declaration with ctx, vhdl_decl
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_CONSTANT_DECL:
        Return proc translate_constant_declaration with ctx, vhdl_decl
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_TYPE_DECL:
        Return proc translate_type_declaration with ctx, vhdl_decl
    End If

    Note: Component declaration - translate to module interface
    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_COMPONENT_DECL:
        Let comp_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "name"
        Let ports be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_decl, "ports"

        Let comp_module be proc create_hir_module with comp_name

        Note: Translate ports to module parameters
        If ports is not equal to 0:
            Let port_count be proc list_length from ListCore with ports
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than port_count:
                Let port_decl be proc list_get from ListCore with ports, i
                Let port_names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "names"
                Let port_mode be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "mode"
                Let port_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "subtype"

                Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, port_type
                Let name_count be proc list_length from ListCore with port_names
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than name_count:
                    Let port_name be proc list_get from ListCore with port_names, j
                    Let port_var be proc create_hir_variable with port_name, type_hir, 0
                    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with port_var, "mode", port_mode

                    Let module_body be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with comp_module, "body"
                    proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, port_var
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While

                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Return comp_module
    End If

    Note: Default - NOP
    Let nop be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_NOP
    Return nop
End Process

Note: ==================== Design Unit Translation ====================

@Reasoning:
A VHDL entity declares the externally-visible interface (ports + generics)
of a hardware module. Lowers to an HIR module with its body holding the
port/generic declarations. ctx.entity_name is set so subsequent
architecture translation can link back to its entity.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_entity" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_entity as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL entity to HIR module interface

    Let entity_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_entity, "name"
    Set ctx.entity_name to entity_name

    Let module be proc create_hir_module with entity_name

    Note: Translate generic parameters
    Let generics be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_entity, "generics"
    If generics is not equal to 0:
        Let generic_count be proc list_length from ListCore with generics
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than generic_count:
            Let generic_decl be proc list_get from ListCore with generics, i
            Let generic_names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with generic_decl, "names"
            Let generic_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with generic_decl, "subtype"

            Let type_hir be proc translate_type with ctx, generic_type
            Let name_count be proc list_length from ListCore with generic_names
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than name_count:
                Let gen_name be proc list_get from ListCore with generic_names, j
                Let gen_var be proc create_hir_variable with gen_name, type_hir, 0
                proc set_attribute from HirNodes with gen_var, "is_generic", 1

                Let module_body be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with module, "body"
                proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, gen_var
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Translate ports
    Let ports be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_entity, "ports"
    If ports is not equal to 0:
        Let port_count be proc list_length from ListCore with ports
        Set i to 0
        While i is less than port_count:
            Let port_decl be proc list_get from ListCore with ports, i
            Let port_names be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "names"
            Let port_mode be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "mode"
            Let port_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with port_decl, "subtype"

            Set type_hir to proc translate_type with ctx, port_type
            Set name_count to proc list_length from ListCore with port_names
            Set j to 0
            While j is less than name_count:
                Let port_name be proc list_get from ListCore with port_names, j
                Let port_var be proc create_hir_variable with port_name, type_hir, 0
                proc set_attribute from HirNodes with port_var, "mode", port_mode
                proc set_attribute from HirNodes with port_var, "is_port", 1

                Set module_body to proc get_attribute from HirNodes with module, "body"
                proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, port_var
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return module
End Process

@Reasoning:
An architecture body provides the implementation of a previously-declared
entity: declarations (signals, types) then concurrent statements (processes,
component instances). Linked to its entity via the architecture-of clause.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_architecture" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_arch as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL architecture to HIR module implementation

    Let arch_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_arch, "name"
    Let entity_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_arch, "entity_name"

    Set ctx.architecture_name to arch_name
    Set ctx.entity_name to entity_name

    Note: Create module for architecture implementation
    Let underscore_str be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "_"
    Let impl_name be proc string_concat from StringPrim with entity_name, underscore_str
    Set impl_name to proc string_concat from StringPrim with impl_name, arch_name

    Let module be proc create_hir_module with impl_name
    Let module_body be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with module, "body"

    Note: Translate declarations
    Let declarations be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_arch, "declarations"
    If declarations is not equal to 0:
        Let decl_count be proc list_length from ListCore with declarations
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than decl_count:
            Let decl be proc list_get from ListCore with declarations, i
            Let decl_hir be proc translate_declaration with ctx, decl
            proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, decl_hir
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Translate concurrent statements
    Let statements be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_arch, "statements"
    Let stmt_count be proc list_length from ListCore with statements
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than stmt_count:
        Let stmt be proc list_get from ListCore with statements, i
        Let stmt_hir be proc translate_concurrent_statement with ctx, stmt
        proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, stmt_hir
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return module
End Process

@Reasoning:
VHDL packages bundle declarations (types, constants, subprograms) for
reuse. Lowers to an HIR module whose body is the declaration list.
Package bodies (separate from headers) supply the implementations later.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_package" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_pkg as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL package to HIR module

    Let pkg_name be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_pkg, "name"

    Let module be proc create_hir_module with pkg_name
    Let module_body be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with module, "body"

    Note: Translate package declarations
    Let declarations be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_pkg, "declarations"
    If declarations is not equal to 0:
        Let decl_count be proc list_length from ListCore with declarations
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than decl_count:
            Let decl be proc list_get from ListCore with declarations, i
            Let decl_hir be proc translate_declaration with ctx, decl
            proc list_append from ListCore with module_body, decl_hir
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Mark as package
    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with module, "is_package", 1

    Return module
End Process

@Reasoning:
Top-level design-unit dispatcher: entity, architecture, package, or
configuration. Routes to the specialised translators above and returns
the resulting HIR module-like node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_design_unit" that takes ctx as Integer, vhdl_unit as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate VHDL design unit to HIR

    Let node_type be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_unit, "type"

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_ENTITY:
        Return proc translate_entity with ctx, vhdl_unit
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_ARCHITECTURE:
        Return proc translate_architecture with ctx, vhdl_unit
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_PACKAGE:
        Return proc translate_package with ctx, vhdl_unit
    End If

    If node_type is equal to VhdlParser.NODE_PACKAGE_BODY:
        Return proc translate_package with ctx, vhdl_unit
    End If

    Note: Default - empty module
    Return proc create_hir_module with "unknown"
End Process

Note: ==================== Main Translation Entry Point ====================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point: creates a fresh context, walks the top-level
design-unit list, returns an HIR module list. Errors propagate
through ctx; the returned list is empty when translation fails.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate" that takes vhdl_ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main translation function - Translate VHDL AST to HIR
    Note: vhdl_ast: Root VHDL AST node from parser
    Note: Returns: HIR root node

    Let ctx be proc create_context

    Note: Create root HIR program node
    Let program be proc create_node from HirNodes with HirNodes.HIR_PROGRAM
    Let modules be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Get design units
    Let design_units be proc get_attribute from HirNodes with vhdl_ast, "design_units"

    Note: Translate each design unit
    Let unit_count be proc list_length from ListCore with design_units
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than unit_count:
        Let unit be proc list_get from ListCore with design_units, i
        Let hir_unit be proc translate_design_unit with ctx, unit
        proc list_append from ListCore with modules, hir_unit
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc set_attribute from HirNodes with program, "modules", modules

    Return program
End Process

Note: ==================== Source-Level Translation Entry Point ====================

@Reasoning:
End-to-end source convenience entry for the VHDL frontend, mirroring
c_to_hir_from_source but following VHDL's lexer-driver shape. Unlike the
list-returning scanners (Verilog/LaTeX), the VHDL lexer is a pull lexer:
create_lexer(source) primes the cursor and next_token(lexer) yields one
whitespace-and-comment-stripped token per call, terminating with a
TOKEN_EOF token that itself must be appended so the parser's
"while current_token_type is not TOKEN_EOF" loop sees the sentinel. This
wrapper therefore builds the token list explicitly, then hands it to the
parser's public parse(tokens, token_count) convenience entry (which
constructs its own parser state) and lowers the resulting design-file
AST through the public translate(ast) entry (which constructs its own
translation context). Returning 0 on null source, lexer-allocation
failure, or token-list-allocation failure matches Runa's nullable-pointer
convention and the dispatcher's documented error convention (a 0 return
is treated as "frontend failed").
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Null-guard source (return 0). create_lexer(source) primes the lexer;
return 0 on failure. Create an empty token list; return 0 on failure.
Loop next_token(lexer): append each token, read its type via
VhdlParser.get_token_type, and stop after appending the TOKEN_EOF token.
parse(tokens, token_count) builds the parser over the list and walks it
to a NODE_DESIGN_FILE AST root. Lower the AST with the public
translate(ast) entry, capturing the HIR program root, and return it.
@End Implementation
Process called "vhdl_to_hir_from_source" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lexer be proc create_lexer from VhdlLexer with source
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let tokens be proc list_create from ListCore
    If tokens is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_count be 0
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        Let token be proc next_token from VhdlLexer with lexer
        proc list_append from ListCore with tokens, token
        Set token_count to token_count plus 1

        Let token_type be proc get_token_type from VhdlParser with token
        If token_type is equal to VhdlLexer.TOKEN_EOF:
            Set scanning to 0
        End If
    End While

    Let ast be proc parse from VhdlParser with tokens, token_count
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir be proc translate with ast

    Return hir
End Process
